# Supabase Configuration
# Get these values from your Supabase project settings: https://supabase.com/dashboard/project/_/settings/api

VITE_SUPABASE_URL=your-project-url-here
VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=your-publishable-key-here

# Public URL of the deployed app (no trailing slash). Password-reset emails use this for the
# link target. If you trigger “Forgot password” on localhost but open the link on your phone,
# you MUST set this to your live URL or the email will point at localhost (or fail). Production
# builds: set on your host (Vercel, etc.) and rebuild.
# VITE_SITE_URL=https://your-domain.com
#
# Email: Subject is edited under Authentication → Email Templates → Reset password.
# The inbox “From” name “Supabase Auth” is replaced only with custom SMTP: Authentication →
# SMTP → set Sender name (e.g. DraftDNA) and smtp_sender_name / from address per Supabase docs.
#
# Supabase Dashboard → Authentication → URL Configuration:
# - Site URL = your live site (not localhost).
# - Redirect URLs: include https://your-domain.com/** and explicitly allow
#   https://your-domain.com/recover-password (wildcard ** usually covers it).
# - Local dev: http://localhost:8080/** (match vite.config server.port).

# Server-only (e.g. scripts/bootstrap-sleeper-ids.ts) — never use VITE_ prefix (would risk bundling).
# Uncomment the next line and paste the service_role secret from Supabase → Settings → API.
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=paste-long-jwt-here

# Auth user UUID(s) allowed to see the “Sync player teams” control in Settings (not secret; mirror ADMIN_SYNC_USER_IDS on Edge).
# Restart `npm run dev` after changing — Vite reads VITE_* only at startup. Comma-separated for multiple admins.
# VITE_SYNC_ADMIN_USER_ID=your-auth-user-uuid
